This paper deals with the vulnerability of spiking neural networks (SNNs) to adversarial attacks, which is a topic related to machine learning and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves classification tasks and deep belief networks, which are related to topics such as machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses the generalization capabilities of SNNs, which is related to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY).
